================================================================================
License split
================================================================================

This is a monorepo. Different parts carry different licenses on purpose:

  * Core hosted server (network copyleft) — GNU AGPL-3.0-or-later
      apps/api           GraphQL API, resolvers, services, ledger
      apps/web           Next.js app (customer PWA, restaurant/rider/admin UIs)
      packages/db        Prisma schema, migrations, seed
      packages/config    shared build/lint config used only by the above

  * SDKs / API clients / shareable libraries (patent grant, ecosystem uptake)
      — Apache License 2.0
      packages/shared    pure, framework-free domain library
                         (money math, geo, hours, order state machine, roles,
                         zod schemas, constants) that a third-party SDK or
                         integrator can import without inheriting AGPL.

The authoritative texts live at the repository root:
  * LICENSE                  — GNU AGPL-3.0-or-later (the "core" license)
  * LICENSE-Apache-2.0.txt   — Apache License 2.0 (the "SDK" license)

Each Apache-2.0 package additionally carries its own LICENSE file and a
`"license"` field in its package.json so the boundary travels with the code
when published. See CONTRIBUTING.md ("Licensing & file headers") for the
per-file SPDX header convention.

